See document .png file for a screenshot of the BASH commands demostrated. Or see following script:
The task was to perform the removal of a userid after a user had left the department they where working in.

suder usermod -g research_team researcher9
ls
pwd
analyst
cd /home/researcher2/projects
chown researcher9 /home/researcher2/projects/projects_r.txt
sudo chown researcher9 /home/researcher2/projects/projects_r.txt
usermod -a -G sales_team researcher9
sudo usermod -a -G sales_team researcher9
sudo userdel researcher9
sudo groupdel researcher9
